menu "breadboard: bb_pub_ota_quiesce"

config BB_PUB_QUIESCE_ON_OTA
    bool "Pause telemetry publishing during update-check/OTA TLS handshake"
    default y
    depends on BB_PUB_AUTOREGISTER
    help
        When enabled, bb_pub_ota_quiesce self-registers at the PRE_HTTP tier
        and installs bb_pub_pause / bb_pub_resume as the pause/resume hooks
        for both bb_update_check and bb_ota (push/pull/boot). This frees
        the heap occupied by in-flight telemetry sinks during the mbedTLS
        handshake, which is critical on heap-tight targets like the ESP32-S2.
        Disable to install the hooks manually via bb_pub_ota_quiesce_init().

endmenu
